get template directory "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
======================================================================

NAME
----

get template directory - Retrieves the absolute path to the directory of the current

SYNOPSIS
--------

Retrieves the absolute path to the directory of the current
[theme](/Glossary#Theme "Glossary"), without the trailing slash.

In the case a child theme is being used, the absolute path to the parent
theme directory will be returned. Use
[`get_stylesheet_directory()`](/Function_Reference/get_stylesheet_directory "Function Reference/get stylesheet directory")
to get the absolute path to the child theme directory.

USAGE
-----

` <?php get_template_directory(); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

This tag has no parameters.

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `` `(string)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   Absolute path to the directory of the current theme (without the
    trailing slash).

EXAMPLES
--------

NOTES
-----

-   Uses:
    [`get_theme_root()`](/Function_Reference/get_theme_root "Function Reference/get theme root")
    to retrieve the absolute path to the themes directory,
    [`get_template()`](/Function_Reference/get_template "Function Reference/get template")
    to retrieve the directory name of the current theme.
-   Uses:
    [`apply_filters()`](/Function_Reference/apply_filters "Function Reference/apply filters")
    to apply the
    [template\_directory](/Plugin_API/Filter_Reference/template_directory "Plugin API/Filter Reference/template directory")
    filters on the resultant path.

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: [1.5.0](/Version_1.5 "Version 1.5")

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`get_template_directory()` is located in `wp-includes/theme.php`.

